<script lang="ts">
  const html: string = "<h1>Table Head</h1>\n\n<p>TableHead is a headless component that renders a <code>&lt;thead&gt;</code> element within a table. It groups header rows that define column labels.</p>\n\n<p>Use this component within a Table to define the header section containing column headings.</p>\n\n<h2>Implementation Notes</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Renders a <code>&lt;thead&gt;</code> element for table header group semantics</li>\n<li>Accepts <code>className</code> for CSS class targeting</li>\n<li>Spreads <code>restProps</code> onto the <code>&lt;thead&gt;</code> element for consumer customization</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Props</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>className</code>: string (default: <code>\"\"</code>) -- CSS class name for the header group</li>\n<li><code>children</code>: slot (required) -- header rows, typically TableRow components with <code>&lt;th&gt;</code> cells</li>\n<li><code>...restProps</code>: unknown -- additional attributes spread onto the <code>&lt;thead&gt;</code> element</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;Table label=\"Users\"&gt;\n  &lt;TableHead&gt;\n    &lt;TableRow&gt;\n      &lt;th&gt;Name&lt;/th&gt;\n      &lt;th&gt;Email&lt;/th&gt;\n    &lt;/TableRow&gt;\n  &lt;/TableHead&gt;\n&lt;/Table&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Keyboard Interactions</h2>\n\n<p>Standard table keyboard interactions.</p>\n\n<h2>ARIA</h2>\n\n<p>No additional ARIA attributes. Header semantics are provided by the <code>&lt;thead&gt;</code> element.</p>\n\n<h2>When to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Use inside Table to wrap the header row(s) that label each column</li>\n<li>Use to group <code>&lt;th&gt;</code> cells with <code>scope=\"col\"</code> that define column headings</li>\n<li>Use to provide a visually distinct header section that screen readers can navigate to</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When Not to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Do not use outside of a Table -- use DataTableHead for DataTable or CalendarTableHead for CalendarTable</li>\n<li>Do not use for footer summary rows -- use TableFoot instead</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Headless</h2>\n\n<p>This headless component renders a <code>&lt;thead&gt;</code> element. The consumer provides all visual styling.</p>\n\n<h2>Styles</h2>\n\n<p>The consumer provides all CSS styling. The component renders with a <code>.table-head</code> class for targeting.</p>\n\n<h2>Testing</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Verify the component renders a <code>&lt;thead&gt;</code> element</li>\n<li>Verify children content is rendered</li>\n<li>Verify pass-through attributes are applied</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Composition</h2>\n\n<p>TableHead is a child of Table, following the Table pattern: Table &gt; TableHead/TableBody/TableFoot &gt; TableRow &gt; TableTD.</p>\n\n<h2>Related components</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>table</code> — a table with rows and columns &lt;table&gt;</li>\n<li><code>table-body</code> — a table interactive grid tbody &lt;tbody&gt;</li>\n<li><code>table-foot</code> — a table interactive grid tfoot &lt;tfoot&gt;</li>\n<li><code>table-row</code> — a table interactive grid row &lt;tr&gt;</li>\n<li><code>table-td</code> — a table interactive grid data cell &lt;td&gt;</li>\n<li><code>table-th</code> — a table interactive grid column &lt;th&gt;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>References</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>MDN thead element: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/thead</li>\n</ul>";
</script>

